Note to the User Casparti on initiating flamewar.

Previous citations of Humboldt are false, please check. Humboldt explicitly did not include Afghanistan in the definition of Central Asia as it does not fall within the band of 5 degrees latitude within the 44.5 degree parallel as stated in his publication. Later works by Khanikoff, however, does also include parts of Iran and Afghanistan into his definition of Central Asia, which is bigger in scope. Kalpak travel" was removed as a source because it is a tourism website, not an academic source..
